Human infection with avian influenza A(H7N9) virus -- update 14 Apr 2014
------------------------------------------------------------
On [11 Apr 2014], the National Health and Family Planning Commission (NHFPC) of China notified WHO of 4 additional laboratory-confirmed cases of human infection with avian influenza A(H7N9) virus.

Details of the cases reported to WHO are as follows:
- an 81-year-old woman from Guangzhou City, Guangdong Province. She became ill on[26 Mar 2014], was admitted to a hospital on [4 Apr 2014] and is currently in a critical condition. She had a history of exposure to poultry.
- a 37-year-old man from Shantou City, Guangdong Province. He became ill on [3 Apr 2014], was admitted to a hospital on [7 Apr 2014] and is currently in a critical condition. He had a history of exposure to live poultry market.
- a 71-year-old woman from Heyuan City, Guangdong Province. She became ill on [1 Apr 2014], was admitted to a hospital on [5 Apr 2014] and is currently in a critical condition. She had a history of exposure to live poultry market.
- a 79-year-old man from Guangzhou City, Guangdong Province. He became ill on [7 Apr 2014], was admitted to a hospital on the same day and is currently in a critical condition. He had a history of exposure to live poultry market.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Marianne Hopp

